column2:
data %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(expcond) %>% 
  furniture::table1("Age" = age,
                    "Gender" = gender,
                    "Race/Ethnicity" = race2,
                    "Degree" = degree,
                    "Setting, parctice" = practsetting,
                    "Setting, school" = schoolsetting,
                    "Practicing, years" = yearsinpractice,
                    "Trainging in ASD (0-100)" = trainingasd,
                    "Culturally/Lingually diverse students" = cldstudents,
                    "ASD knowledge, precieved (0 - 100)" = perceivedasdknowledge,
                    "ASD knowledge, percent correct (0 - 100)" = askspr_total_score*100/25,
                    "ASD knowledge, standardized measure" = askspr_stand_score,
                    "Rating of ASD likelyhood (0-100)" = asd_likely,
                    "Confidence in Rating of ASD likelyhood (0-100)" = asd_conf,
                    asd_conf,
                    askspr_total_score,
                    askspr_stand_score,
                    na.rm = FALSE,
                    total = FALSE,
                    test = TRUE,
                    digits = 2,
                    output = "markdown",
                    caption = "Participant Dempographic Summary, by Vignette Condition")
Breusch-Pagan Test of Heteroskedasticity suggests `var.equal = FALSE` in oneway.test() for: Rating.of.ASD.likelyhood..0.100.
